a."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":32,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":63,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas de Helbeck I was born in 1227, in Warcop, Westmorland, England as the son of Robert de Helbeck. He married Alicia de Musgrave in Westmorland, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1291, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1227–1291":"1227–1291","1226–1289":"1226–1289","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1251–1297":"1251–1297","1255–1276":"1255–1276","1256–Female":"1256–Surnud","1184–Male":"1184–Surnud","October 1289":"oktoober 1289","1297":"1297","Cir 1256":"1256","1230":"1230","1251":"1251","1184":"1184","1291":"1291","1290":"1290","1227":"1227","1259":"1259","1226":"1226","1256":"1256","1289":"1289","1255":"1255","1276":"1276","after 1276":"pärast 1276","Warcop, Westmoreland, England":"Warcop, Westmorland, England","Somme, Picardy, France":"Som